02:26.439 --> 02:28.566
<font color="#D900D9">(CHATTERING IN FRENCH)</font>

06:57.084 --> 06:59.253
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLING)</font>

08:15.955 --> 08:18.833
<font color="#D900D9">(CHURCH BELLS TOLL)</font>

10:29.296 --> 10:31.340
<font color="#808080">NEIL:</font> My sweet love.

10:35.803 --> 10:38.013
At last.

10:58.075 --> 10:59.910
My hope.

11:09.795 --> 11:11.881
How I loved you.

11:32.693 --> 11:35.070
<font color="#D900D9">(CHATTERING)</font>

12:50.354 --> 12:53.274
<font color="#808080">NEIGHBOUR:</font> How long have you been here?

12:54.858 --> 12:56.777
- A couple of months.
- Oh.

12:56.902 --> 12:58.904
How do you like it so far?

12:59.697 --> 13:00.739
I like it.

13:02.449 --> 13:05.077
- And do you have any children?
- I have a daughter.

13:05.661 --> 13:08.205
She's ten.

13:08.330 --> 13:11.000
I bet it's hard being a single mum.

13:11.125 --> 13:13.294
I know my daughter's a little younger,

13:13.419 --> 13:15.921
but it would be fun for them
to get together maybe.

13:16.046 --> 13:19.091
It's kind of a hard age to move away.

17:01.647 --> 17:04.775
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> - What's going on here?
- We're doing a little remedial work.

17:05.317 --> 17:07.277
Remedial work?

17:08.237 --> 17:10.071
<font color="#808080">NEIL:</font> We're looking to make sure
there's no toxins.

17:10.196 --> 17:12.366
I got stuff on my house.

17:12.991 --> 17:14.492
Kids acting strange.

17:16.662 --> 17:21.458
Sometimes we see tar
coming out of the cracks in the patio.

17:23.585 --> 17:26.213
The neighbours here,
they had their house in escrow.

17:26.338 --> 17:28.382
They pulled out.

17:29.591 --> 17:32.135
- The buyers pulled out.
- Yeah.

17:34.972 --> 17:36.473
That's too bad.

17:37.182 --> 17:40.477
The reports from the lab came in.

17:40.602 --> 17:44.064
It showed the presence of lead
and cadmium in the surface soil

17:44.189 --> 17:46.984
and in the dust in the school-yards.

18:51.423 --> 18:53.675
<font color="#D900D9">(I DISTANT BRASS BAND MUSIC)</font>

19:28.627 --> 19:30.253
<font color="#808080">GIRL:</font> I've had it blonde

19:30.379 --> 19:32.881
and brown and pink and red.

19:34.007 --> 19:37.719
Me, I could never dye my hair,
unless my mum says I can.

19:38.804 --> 19:41.765
My mum doesn't care.
My mum's pretty cool.

19:41.890 --> 19:43.725
<font color="#D900D9">(I CHILDREN CHANTING)</font>

19:58.323 --> 19:59.866
<font color="#D900D9">(CAR HORN)</font>

20:45.912 --> 20:47.748
Of course.

21:43.637 --> 21:45.514
<font color="#808080">PASTOR:</font> There is a love

21:46.056 --> 21:51.186
that's like a stream that goes dry
when rain no longer feeds it.

21:51.978 --> 21:54.272
But there is a love

21:54.397 --> 21:57.901
that is like a spring
coming up from the earth.

21:58.819 --> 22:01.196
The first is human love,
the second is divine love

22:01.321 --> 22:03.740
and has its source above.

22:05.659 --> 22:10.539
The husband is to love his wife
as Christ loved the church,

22:10.664 --> 22:12.791
and give his life for her.

22:14.793 --> 22:18.672
He does not <i>find</i> her lovely,
he <i>makes</i> her lovely.

22:19.965 --> 22:22.759
But there is a grace
that comes in such a marriage.

22:23.468 --> 22:25.720
<font color="#808080">MARINA:</font> I got married when I was 17.

22:27.722 --> 22:29.683
I had a child.

22:31.393 --> 22:35.480
But my husband
started running after other women.

22:36.398 --> 22:39.484
He left us and went
to the Canary Islands.

22:41.319 --> 22:44.781
Other priests have told me
that in the eyes of the church

22:44.906 --> 22:47.868
I'm still married to that man.

22:51.121 --> 22:53.748
They said I couldn't have
the sacraments.

22:59.421 --> 23:01.548
I want to be a wife.

23:20.442 --> 23:22.903
<font color="#808080">GIRL:</font> I don't even know
why I was with him in the first place.

23:24.321 --> 23:27.032
And then it sunk in.

23:29.159 --> 23:34.289
I didn't really want to tell my dad,
because I knew he would start yelling,

23:34.414 --> 23:36.583
yelling very loudly, and...

23:38.418 --> 23:40.378
I'd never give her up.

23:41.087 --> 23:42.714
Ever.

23:57.812 --> 23:59.898
<font color="#D900D9">(PRIEST'S WORDS IN SPANISH...)</font>

25:41.708 --> 25:44.753
<font color="#D900D9">(MARINA'S WORDS IN FRENCH...)</font>

26:50.652 --> 26:52.737
<font color="#D900D9">(HUMS TUNE)</font>

28:45.600 --> 28:47.894
<font color="#D900D9">(CHANTS IN FRENCH)</font>

29:34.190 --> 29:37.652
You see that red band
in the sky right there?

29:37.777 --> 29:40.280
And you see that blue down below it?

29:40.405 --> 29:43.324
That's the earth's shadow
on the atmosphere.

29:45.785 --> 29:47.996
Look. You see
what I'm talking about?

29:48.121 --> 29:50.790
Stop for a second.
You see?

30:17.358 --> 30:19.235
<font color="#808080">MARINA:</font> Tatiana...

30:39.839 --> 30:42.342
<font color="#D900D9">(I SINGING GENTLY)</font>

31:57.375 --> 31:59.836
<font color="#808080">OLD WOMAN:</font> Father,
I'm going to pray for you.

31:59.961 --> 32:01.796
Thank you very much.

32:01.921 --> 32:05.007
So you will receive the gift of joy.

32:06.300 --> 32:08.136
Me?

32:09.720 --> 32:12.014
Because you're so unhappy.

32:19.230 --> 32:21.899
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Do you get lonely all the time,
or most of the time

32:22.024 --> 32:23.818
when there ain't nobody around?

32:28.322 --> 32:30.116
So, what you got to say about it?

32:31.367 --> 32:33.161
You gotta have a little more excitement.

32:33.286 --> 32:36.372
Just like when me and you are around,
and there ain't nobody around.

32:36.497 --> 32:39.000
Hey! The power hits you, brother.

32:39.125 --> 32:42.128
It always hits me. You can just say,
hey, power, and it hits me.

32:42.253 --> 32:43.629
Hits me before I can get it out.

32:43.754 --> 32:45.965
<font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKS IN TONGUES)</font>

32:46.090 --> 32:50.720
See, the devil don't know what I'm saying.
And you won't know, and I won't know.

32:50.845 --> 32:55.224
I can feel the warmth of the light, brother.

32:55.349 --> 32:59.187
That's spiritual.
I'm feeling more than just natural light.

32:59.312 --> 33:01.189
Feeling the spiritual light, see?

33:01.898 --> 33:05.359
I can almost touch that light,
coming right from the sky.

33:13.534 --> 33:15.495
The parish has grown a lot,

33:15.620 --> 33:20.500
and we really need more room
for the community to get together.

33:20.625 --> 33:24.795
We have plays, we have dinners,
we have parties.

33:24.921 --> 33:29.258
We have CCD in the parish hall.

33:38.851 --> 33:41.395
<font color="#D900D9">(<font color="#808080">PRIEST:</font> IN SPANISH...)</font>

33:46.150 --> 33:48.152
If I would have known it was there...

33:51.656 --> 33:52.907
Thank you.

34:01.666 --> 34:03.292
Everything that's happening...

34:03.417 --> 34:06.128
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT DIALOGUE...)</font>

34:48.420 --> 34:51.966
<font color="#808080">PASTOR:</font> Man is in revolt against God.

34:52.091 --> 34:55.928
The prophet Hosea saw
in the breakdown of his marriage

34:56.053 --> 34:58.764
the spiritual infidelity of his people.

34:58.889 --> 35:03.019
In that broken marriage,
we see the pattern of our world.

35:03.144 --> 35:06.480
We wish to live
inside the safety of the laws.

35:06.606 --> 35:09.025
We fear to choose.

35:09.150 --> 35:12.194
Jesus insists on choice.

35:12.320 --> 35:16.282
The one thing he condemns utterly
is avoiding the choice.

35:17.283 --> 35:20.077
To choose is to commit yourself,

35:20.202 --> 35:24.707
and to commit yourself
is to run the risk of failure,

35:24.832 --> 35:27.835
the risk of sin, the risk of betrayal,

35:27.960 --> 35:30.921
but Jesus can deal with all of those.

35:31.047 --> 35:33.633
Forgiveness he never denies us.

35:34.675 --> 35:37.845
The man who makes a mistake
can repent.

35:39.138 --> 35:40.681
But the man who hesitates,

35:40.806 --> 35:43.100
who does nothing,

35:43.225 --> 35:47.813
who buries his talent
in the earth with him,

35:47.938 --> 35:50.107
he can do nothing.

35:54.236 --> 35:56.864
<font color="#D900D9">(<font color="#808080">MARINA:</font> IN FRENCH...)</font>

38:31.185 --> 38:33.646
<font color="#D900D9">(BIRDSONG)</font>

39:05.427 --> 39:07.638
<font color="#D900D9">(CHATTERING)</font>

39:13.310 --> 39:16.647
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> These guys who live around here,
they're perfectly happy

39:16.772 --> 39:19.942
until somebody comes around
asking questions,

39:20.067 --> 39:23.237
and it makes everybody nervous,
because...

39:25.823 --> 39:28.784
Ain't this is our property?
Can't we do what we want with it?

39:28.909 --> 39:31.704
I tell my husband to get us out of here,
but where we gonna go?

39:38.627 --> 39:41.964
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> They got all these big time lawyers,
and we can't get no help.

39:44.091 --> 39:46.260
Even the dog is acting funny.

40:18.667 --> 40:20.920
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> We've been on this house
for a long time.

40:36.977 --> 40:39.063
<font color="#D900D9">(MARINA SPEAKS FRENCH SOFTLY...)</font>

41:48.590 --> 41:50.467
You're out at the ranch up there?

41:52.428 --> 41:53.929
I've been there for some time.

41:57.016 --> 42:00.352
<font color="#808080">NEIL:</font> I have to look at
some of these creeks and rivers.

42:03.814 --> 42:06.358
You talk to my sister, right?

42:19.079 --> 42:23.042
<font color="#808080">NEIL:</font> I'm going over
to the tall grass prairie now.

42:39.183 --> 42:42.436
<font color="#808080">JANE:</font> The ranch is going into receivership.

42:42.561 --> 42:44.897
It's going bankrupt.

42:49.193 --> 42:54.782
And he claimed he didn't want
to have kids while he was in school.

42:54.907 --> 42:56.533
<font color="#808080">NEIL:</font> She hadn't changed.

42:56.658 --> 43:00.496
<font color="#808080">JANE:</font> So many student loans,
gambling debts,

43:00.621 --> 43:03.791
and this ranch that's falling apart.

43:06.043 --> 43:08.378
I caught you on the right day.

43:11.799 --> 43:12.841
Kind.

45:01.074 --> 45:03.702
<font color="#808080">JANE:</font> I had a child.

45:06.079 --> 45:07.873
A little girl.

45:16.632 --> 45:18.425
She died.

45:21.553 --> 45:23.222
My father...

45:24.181 --> 45:25.724
he said to read Romans.

45:30.520 --> 45:33.315
All things work together for good.

45:36.777 --> 45:38.654
He believed that.

45:41.448 --> 45:43.533
Will you pray with me?

45:55.504 --> 45:57.547
<font color="#808080">NEIL:</font> I had no faith.

46:02.594 --> 46:04.513
You knew.

46:08.517 --> 46:10.519
Were you afraid?

46:17.818 --> 46:21.280
<font color="#808080">JANE:</font> My mother says
I'm chasing moonbeams.

46:21.405 --> 46:24.032
- Is that what she said?
- Mm-hmm.

46:26.034 --> 46:32.666
I told her I'd rather have a moonbeam
than the life I had before.

46:57.399 --> 46:59.443
<font color="#808080">JANE:</font> Do you want this?

47:05.741 --> 47:07.826
Do you know what you want?

47:13.749 --> 47:18.170
I can't afford to make mistakes
with men any more.

47:27.012 --> 47:29.639
I want you to come more often.

47:30.891 --> 47:32.809
Can you?

47:36.897 --> 47:39.316
<font color="#D900D9">(MURMURS)</font> I've been waiting for you.

47:41.485 --> 47:43.070
I felt wild.

47:43.195 --> 47:45.405
- What?
- I don't know. What are you laughing at?

47:45.530 --> 47:47.032
You.

47:47.157 --> 47:49.868
- Me?
- You make me laugh.

47:51.119 --> 47:53.205
You make me happy.

48:00.212 --> 48:02.255
You took me.

48:12.057 --> 48:13.725
No.

48:26.279 --> 48:27.823
Girl.

48:31.910 --> 48:33.954
Little girl.

48:39.000 --> 48:40.877
Fool.

49:13.910 --> 49:15.537
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

49:32.471 --> 49:34.431
Here I am.

49:45.775 --> 49:47.611
Yes.

52:26.936 --> 52:29.147
<font color="#808080">NEIL:</font> Tell her.

52:37.405 --> 52:39.449
<font color="#D900D9">(CLANGING)</font>

52:50.043 --> 52:51.753
<font color="#D900D9">(WHIRRING)</font>

54:02.866 --> 54:04.909
<font color="#D900D9">(HORSE SNORTS)</font>

54:19.549 --> 54:21.718
I trust you.

54:37.734 --> 54:40.278
I want to be your wife.

54:51.039 --> 54:53.124
I love you.

56:08.825 --> 56:10.827
Walk away.

56:19.794 --> 56:21.880
I thought I knew you.

56:27.552 --> 56:30.305
Now I don't think you ever were.

56:43.443 --> 56:45.403
What we had was nothing.

56:50.283 --> 56:52.744
You made it into nothing.

56:56.831 --> 56:58.625
Pleasure.

57:02.795 --> 57:04.672
Lust.

57:41.542 --> 57:43.252
Ma'am, if you'll come over here.

57:43.378 --> 57:45.922
Sir, if you'll be on this side, please.

57:46.047 --> 57:48.049
Y'all have rings for each other?
OK.

57:48.967 --> 57:51.552
To love, honour and cherish you.

57:54.055 --> 57:56.599
Be faithful only to you.

57:57.850 --> 57:59.686
As long as we both shall live.

58:01.437 --> 58:04.232
<font color="#D900D9">(JUSTICE OF THE PEACE)</font> And I do promise
before these witnesses...

58:04.357 --> 58:06.651
<font color="#808080">MARINA:</font> And I do promise
before these witnesses...

58:06.776 --> 58:09.195
<font color="#808080">JUSTICE:</font> To love,
honour, and cherish you.

58:09.320 --> 58:11.739
<font color="#808080">MARINA:</font> To love, honour
and cherish you.

58:11.864 --> 58:13.825
<font color="#808080">JUSTICE:</font> Be faithful
only to you.

58:13.950 --> 58:16.536
<font color="#808080">MARINA:</font> Be faithful only to you.

58:16.661 --> 58:18.496
<font color="#808080">JUSTICE:</font> As long as we both shall live.

58:19.372 --> 58:21.582
<font color="#808080">MARINA:</font> As long as we both
shall live.

01:00:04.268 --> 01:00:06.687
<font color="#D900D9">(I SINGS IN FRENCH)</font>

01:02:59.402 --> 01:03:00.861
<font color="#808080">PASTOR:</font> Awaken the love.

01:03:04.156 --> 01:03:05.992
The divine presence...

01:03:07.868 --> 01:03:10.913
...which sleeps in each man,
each woman.

01:03:13.124 --> 01:03:15.459
You say,

01:03:15.584 --> 01:03:20.298
Christ said this, Christ said that.
What do you say?

01:03:22.133 --> 01:03:24.760
And what you say,

01:03:24.885 --> 01:03:27.179
does it come from God within?

01:03:29.390 --> 01:03:33.352
Answer that which is of God,

01:03:33.477 --> 01:03:35.479
in every woman, every man.

01:03:38.024 --> 01:03:42.695
Know each other in that love
that never changes.

01:04:09.055 --> 01:04:11.724
<font color="#808080">DOCTOR:</font> I'd like to show you
here on the monitor...

01:04:12.683 --> 01:04:17.938
This is the area of your uterus
and the IUD that you have in place there.

01:04:18.606 --> 01:04:22.985
We feel like one of the less risky
procedures that we can do

01:04:23.110 --> 01:04:25.654
is to remove this device,

01:04:25.780 --> 01:04:28.783
and see if those symptoms
don't resolve.

01:04:29.700 --> 01:04:33.996
I think something that you
and your husband need to consider

01:04:34.121 --> 01:04:36.832
is with the absence of the IUD,

01:04:36.957 --> 01:04:40.753
is this a time that you might want
to think about children?

01:04:40.878 --> 01:04:43.672
Or is there another means
for contraception?

01:04:43.798 --> 01:04:47.426
So, I don't need to have
a hysterectomy?

01:04:47.551 --> 01:04:49.720
That's the good news.

01:04:52.390 --> 01:04:54.475
Thank you.

01:05:10.741 --> 01:05:13.285
<font color="#808080">DOCTOR:</font> So,
would you like to have children?

01:05:15.746 --> 01:05:17.498
Someday.

01:05:59.123 --> 01:06:03.127
<font color="#808080">PASTOR:</font> God gave us marriage
as a holy mystery,

01:06:03.252 --> 01:06:06.255
in which a man and woman
are joined together

01:06:07.214 --> 01:06:09.300
and become one.

01:06:10.468 --> 01:06:13.053
And with affection and tenderness

01:06:13.179 --> 01:06:16.390
freely give themselves to each other.

01:06:17.475 --> 01:06:19.143
<font color="#808080">NEIL:</font> This ring I give you...

01:06:19.268 --> 01:06:22.938
<font color="#808080">PASTOR:</font> Is a sign of our constant faith.

01:06:23.063 --> 01:06:25.024
<font color="#808080">NEIL:</font> ...is a sign
of our constant faith.

01:06:25.149 --> 01:06:27.443
<font color="#808080">PASTOR:</font> And abiding love.

01:06:27.568 --> 01:06:29.570
<font color="#808080">NEIL:</font> And abiding love.

01:07:09.527 --> 01:07:11.403
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

01:07:18.244 --> 01:07:19.995
Go.

01:11:45.511 --> 01:11:47.930
<font color="#D900D9">(CHILDREN CHATTERING)</font>

01:12:18.210 --> 01:12:20.003
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> We pray thy blessings
upon them,

01:12:20.128 --> 01:12:22.130
and upon this food
which we are about to eat.

01:12:26.468 --> 01:12:28.136
<font color="#D900D9">(CHATTERING)</font>

01:12:29.221 --> 01:12:30.806
Would you like one?

01:13:20.439 --> 01:13:22.274
<font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKS IN ITALIAN...)</font>

01:15:00.122 --> 01:15:01.581
Come on.

01:15:01.707 --> 01:15:03.583
Come on, baby.

01:15:03.709 --> 01:15:05.961
<font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKS ITALIAN...)</font>

01:16:36.093 --> 01:16:39.679
<font color="#D900D9">(<font color="#808080">MARINA:</font> IN FRENCH...)</font>

01:17:53.003 --> 01:17:55.297
<font color="#808080">PRISONER:</font> Things have gotten worse.

01:18:10.854 --> 01:18:13.023
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT DIALOGUE...)</font>

01:18:36.087 --> 01:18:38.632
I don't understand it.
I don't know what happened. I was drunk.

01:18:38.757 --> 01:18:43.511
If I had done this, I'm not saying I did,
I might've, I could've.

01:18:46.097 --> 01:18:49.267
I'm asking for forgiveness, Father.

01:18:49.392 --> 01:18:51.770
I can't... I can't help...

01:18:52.812 --> 01:18:56.691
I can't help myself. If you need me
to kneel down, I'll kneel down.

01:18:58.735 --> 01:19:00.237
I want to be free.

01:19:06.326 --> 01:19:10.580
That sun is just right in my eyes.

01:19:12.457 --> 01:19:16.503
I can fight, I will fight.
I can fight with my feet and hands.

01:19:16.628 --> 01:19:19.631
They think they're really
about something, but they ain't.

01:20:00.672 --> 01:20:03.717
You gonna open that bible
and preach to me now?

01:20:15.145 --> 01:20:16.604
<font color="#D900D9">(IN SPANISH...)</font>

01:20:53.224 --> 01:20:56.603
Lover boy! Where are you?

01:20:58.146 --> 01:21:00.106
<font color="#D900D9">(DOOR BELL RINGS)</font>

01:21:13.370 --> 01:21:15.997
<font color="#808080">PASTOR:</font> Love is not only a feeling.

01:21:17.082 --> 01:21:19.834
Love is a duty.
You <i>shall</i> love.

01:21:21.586 --> 01:21:22.796
Love is a command.

01:21:23.380 --> 01:21:27.467
And you say,
I can't command my emotions.

01:21:27.592 --> 01:21:29.803
They come and go like clouds.

01:21:30.804 --> 01:21:33.807
To that, Christ says: You shall love.

01:21:34.557 --> 01:21:36.976
Whether you like it or not.

01:21:38.395 --> 01:21:40.897
You fear your love has died.

01:21:44.901 --> 01:21:49.030
It perhaps is waiting to be transformed
into something higher.

01:21:50.782 --> 01:21:53.243
<font color="#D900D9">(PRIEST CONTINUES PREACHING...)</font>

01:22:11.261 --> 01:22:14.305
<font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKS FRENCH...)</font>

01:23:51.611 --> 01:23:53.530
He's killing me!

01:23:59.786 --> 01:24:01.204
I'm sorry.

01:24:29.232 --> 01:24:31.401
You want me to die? Here!

01:24:36.364 --> 01:24:38.491
Why don't you have them?

01:25:12.942 --> 01:25:14.611
I'm frightened.

01:25:21.743 --> 01:25:22.744
OK.

01:25:39.052 --> 01:25:42.180
<font color="#D900D9">(<font color="#808080">PRIEST:</font> IN SPANISH...)</font>

01:26:00.573 --> 01:26:02.617
<font color="#808080">MARINA:</font> Give me your blessing, Father.

01:26:07.664 --> 01:26:09.791
I've hurt people.

01:26:16.422 --> 01:26:18.883
I know what I am.

01:26:25.473 --> 01:26:28.059
- The body of Christ.
- Amen.

01:26:29.268 --> 01:26:31.145
The blood of Christ.

01:26:40.697 --> 01:26:43.574
<font color="#D900D9">(<font color="#808080">MARINA:</font> IN FRENCH...)</font>

01:27:52.643 --> 01:27:54.645
I thought you went away.

01:32:49.690 --> 01:32:54.612
<font color="#D900D9">(LOW RUMBLING...)</font>

01:33:04.455 --> 01:33:06.332
Forgive me.

01:33:34.527 --> 01:33:37.988
<font color="#D900D9">(MARINA BEGS)</font> Please.

01:33:38.114 --> 01:33:41.867
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT DIALOGUE...)</font>

01:33:57.925 --> 01:34:00.386
<font color="#D900D9">(LOW RUMBLING CONTINUES FAINTLY...)</font>

01:34:55.566 --> 01:34:59.570
<font color="#D900D9">(RUMBLING FADES)</font>

01:35:22.343 --> 01:35:25.804
<font color="#808080">LAWYER:</font> Don't take up with anybody
during the first six months.

01:35:27.556 --> 01:35:29.725
Don't stop talking to people.

01:35:29.850 --> 01:35:33.812
That's the first mistake that I see
people make in my practice.

01:35:33.938 --> 01:35:37.524
Sometimes you eat the bear,
and sometimes the bear eats you.

01:35:37.650 --> 01:35:40.194
You can't feel sorry for yourself.

01:35:41.820 --> 01:35:43.489
Like I explained earlier,

01:35:43.614 --> 01:35:47.076
once we get her served
that'll start the process.

01:35:47.201 --> 01:35:50.412
Because there's no children involved,
this could be a fairly rapid process,

01:35:50.537 --> 01:35:51.914
if that's what you want.

01:35:53.249 --> 01:35:56.043
I don't want you to lose hope...

01:35:56.168 --> 01:35:57.419
<font color="#D900D9">(DIALOGUE FADES)</font>

01:36:20.276 --> 01:36:21.944
<font color="#808080">PASTOR:</font> It's very hard to be the...

01:36:23.153 --> 01:36:26.282
the one who loves less,
the one who's stronger.

01:36:28.742 --> 01:36:31.328
You have to struggle with yourself.

01:36:32.496 --> 01:36:38.294
You have to struggle
with your own... strength.

01:36:55.477 --> 01:36:57.187
<font color="#808080">NEIL:</font> Why?

01:37:15.622 --> 01:37:17.499
I saw you.

01:37:23.672 --> 01:37:25.632
Again.

01:37:34.350 --> 01:37:37.144
They are sending me away.
I won't be here for long.

01:37:37.269 --> 01:37:39.188
They're sending me
to western Kansas.

01:37:39.313 --> 01:37:42.316
Western Kansas? What are you
gonna do in western Kansas?

01:37:43.359 --> 01:37:46.403
A lot of people around here
are going to be missing you.

01:37:48.364 --> 01:37:52.159
I think we need people like you
here in Bartlesville.

01:37:52.284 --> 01:37:55.329
To preach the gospel.
That's why we have churches.

01:38:20.062 --> 01:38:21.105
<font color="#D900D9">(IN SPANISH...)</font>

01:38:37.955 --> 01:38:40.958
I feel a lot of burning, you know.

01:38:41.083 --> 01:38:43.210
I have a spot here.

01:38:50.426 --> 01:38:52.803
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT DIALOGUE...)</font>

01:38:57.224 --> 01:39:02.062
I pray, but sometimes I don't hear him.
I don't think he hears me.

01:39:53.238 --> 01:39:57.868
<font color="#D900D9">(MURMURS OF CONVERSATION...)</font>

